 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'gep13', 'comment_id': 721566717.0, 'datetime': '2020-11-04 07:42:27+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': '@username_0 why are these necessary?\r\n\r\nIf I recall correctly, the original osx/windows/linux URL\'s were used for a while, but they were then replaced with the powershell/bash ones.  Those original redirects were left in place in case anyone was using them, but everywhere that we "owned" starting using the powershell/bash links.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'pascalberger', 'comment_id': 721567802.0, 'datetime': '2020-11-04 07:45:08+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': "Currently in docs the OS ones are used for .NET Framework (https://cakebuild.net/docs/running-builds/runners/cake-runner-for-dotnet-framework#bootstrapping-for-cake-runner-for.net-framework). We should either provide OS redirects for every bootstrapper, or adopt docs to use PowerShell / Bash redirects. I'm also OK to update docs to move away from the OS redirects.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'gep13', 'comment_id': 721569084.0, 'datetime': '2020-11-04 07:48:15+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': 'Hmm, ok, fair enough.  In which case, this makes sense.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}]

